tika.dc.description:
New York Times bestselling author Sherryl Woods blends danger and intrigue in this readerfavorite adventure romance.

Fearless engineer Cara Scott had set out to discover why her wayward site manager, Rod Craig, hadn't reported in for weeks. The next thing she knew, she was lost in a steaming Mexican jungle, on the run from danger and locked in sensual battle with her arrogant rogue of an employee. Clearly, she was in over her head!

A rugged individualist, Rod was used to oneman campaigns. Cara's interference sparked his ire...and his reluctant ardor. Suddenly, tamingand claimingthis strongwilled woman seemed more important to him than independence. Suddenly, he was in love, in jeopardy, in a sweatall in all, in way too deep!

Previously published.
